# Git commits (no Co-authored-by trailer)

- Use **only** simple one-line commits: `git commit -m "your message here"`.
- **Do not** pass `--trailer "Co-authored-by: Cursor <cursoragent@cursor.com>"` or any other `Co-authored-by` trailer unless a human explicitly asks for it.
- **Do not** add a `Co-authored-by:` line to commit message bodies for routine work.

If this repository has hooks enabled (`git config core.hooksPath .githooks`), `prepare-commit-msg` strips the Cursor trailer; still avoid passing trailers so history stays clean.
